1 > \epsilon > 0
Y_n
P(Y \ge \epsilon) = P(X_1\ge \epsilon \text{ & }\cdots\text{ & }X_n \ge \epsilon) = (1 - \epsilon)^n.
P(Y \ge \epsilon) = 0
P(Y = 0) = 1
P(Y \ge \epsilon) \le \lim_{n \to \infty} (1 - \epsilon)^n = 0.
